COVID-19 Status 💉 🦠

As of 2:38PM PT yesterday, over 1.8 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 29.6 thousand have died.

In the last day, 927 new infections were reported and 7 deaths. Currently 1,549 are in the hospital and 466 are in the ICU. This is trending downwards.

Fortunately, 60.3 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 12 years and older, 5.9% have their 1st shot and 13.1% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is slowing down, but there are 6.9 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~126 days for new deliveries to get into arms.

At the current rate, Canadians should achieve herd immunity around Dec-07 when 80% of the entire population is fully vaccinated. There is no approved vaccine for children aged 11 or younger.
